<_X_chapter sid="EZK 40">
<verse sid="EZK 40:1"/>And it happened in the twenty-fifth year of our captivity, in the first month, on the tenth of the month, in the fourteenth year after the city fell, on that day the hand of the Lord came upon me and brought me<verse eid="EZK 40:1"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:2"/>in a divine vision into the land of Israel and set me upon a very high mountain, and upon it was something like a construction of a city, opposite.<verse eid="EZK 40:2"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:3"/>And he brought me there, and, behold, a man, and his appearance was like an appearance of flashing bronze, and in his hand was a builders' cord and a measuring reed, and he stood by the gate.<verse eid="EZK 40:3"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:4"/>And the man said to me, "Have you seen, son of man? Look with your eyes, and listen with your ears, and set out into your heart all that I show you, for you have entered here in order to show you, and you shall show all that you see to the house of Israel."<verse eid="EZK 40:4"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:5"/>And behold, an enclosing wall outside the house all around, and in the hand of the man was a reed, the measure of six cubits, in a cubit and a handbreadth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:5</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'in a cubit and a handbreadth':  I.e. the so-called long cubit</char></note>, and he measured the outer wall; its breadth was equal to the reed, and its elevation was equal to the reed.<verse eid="EZK 40:5"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:6"/>And he went into the gate that looks to the east by seven steps and measured the thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:6</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note>, six on one side and six on the other, and the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:6</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the gate was equal to the reed.<verse eid="EZK 40:6"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:7"/>And the thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> was equal to the reed in length and equal to the reed in breadth, and the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> to the middle of the thaielatha<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'recesses'?</char></note> was six cubits, and the second thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> was equal to the reed in breadth and equal to the reed in length, and the ailam was five cubits,<verse eid="EZK 40:7"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:8"/>and the third thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> was equal to the reed in breadth and equal to the reed in length.<verse eid="EZK 40:8"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:9"/>And the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the gateway near the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the gate was eight cubits, and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> aileu<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'its doorpost'</char></note> were two cubits, and the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the gate was within.<verse eid="EZK 40:9"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:10"/>And the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> of the gate were opposite a thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note>, three on one side and three on the other, and the three had one measure, and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> had one measure on one side and on the other.<verse eid="EZK 40:10"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:11"/>And he measured the breadth of the door of the gateway ten cubits and the width of the gateway thirteen cubits.<verse eid="EZK 40:11"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:12"/>And there was a cubit being gathered<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:12</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'a cubit being gathered':  Perhaps 'reduced by a cubit'</char></note> in front of the theim<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:12</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> on one side and on the other, and the thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:12</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> was six cubits on one side and six cubits on the other.<verse eid="EZK 40:12"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:13"/>And he measured the gate from the wall of the thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:13</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> to the wall of the thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:13</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> in breadth, twenty-five cubits; this gate was upon a gate.<verse eid="EZK 40:13"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:14"/>And the atrium of the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the gate was sixty cubits; the gate had twenty theim<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> all around,<verse eid="EZK 40:14"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:15"/>and the atrium of the outside gate to the atrium of ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:15</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> of the inside gate was fifty cubits.<verse eid="EZK 40:15"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:16"/>And covered windows were on the theim<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note> and upon the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> inside the gate of the court all around, and likewise the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> had windows all around inside, and on the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch(es) '</char></note> were palms on one side and on the other.<verse eid="EZK 40:16"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:17"/>And he brought me into the outer court, and behold, shrine-carriers' chambers and colonnades around the court; thirty shrine-carriers' chambers were in the colonnades.<verse eid="EZK 40:17"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:18"/>And the colonnades were along the side of the gates, along the length of the gates was the lower colonnade.<verse eid="EZK 40:18"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:19"/>And he measured the breadth of the court from the atrium of the outer gate from the inside up to the atrium of the gate that looks out, one hundred cubits belonging to the one that looks to the east. And he brought me up to the north.<verse eid="EZK 40:19"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:20"/>And behold, the outer court had a gate that looks to the north, and he measured it, its length and breadth,<verse eid="EZK 40:20"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:21"/>and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> thee<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'niche(s) '</char></note>, three on one side and three on the other, and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> aileu<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'its doorpost'</char></note> and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> ail-ammo<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'its porch'</char></note> and its palms, and they were like the measurements of the gate that looks east, fifty cubits, its length and twenty-five cubits, its width.<verse eid="EZK 40:21"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:22"/>And its windows and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:22</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> ailammo<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:22</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'its porch'</char></note> and its palms were just as the gate that looks to the east, and on seven rungs they would ascend upon it, and the<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:22</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Greek = plural</char></note> ailammo<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">40:22</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'its porch'</char></note> were inside.<verse eid="EZK 40:22"/>

<verse sid="EZK 40:23"/>And the inner court had a gate that looks upon the gate of the north like the gate that looks to the east, and he measured the court from gate to gate, one hundred cubits.<verse eid="EZK 40:23"/>

