<_X_chapter sid="EZK 48">
<verse sid="EZK 48:1"/>And these are the names of the tribes: from the beginning, which is northward along the part of the descent of that which cuts all round, to the entrance of Hemath, court of Ainan, borders of Damascus northward along the part of Hemath Court: also eastward as far as the sea shall belong to them: of Dan, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:1</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:1"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:2"/>And from the borders of Dan, those eastward as far as those seaward: of Aser, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:2</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:2"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:3"/>And from the borders of Aser, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Nephthali, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:3</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:3"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:4"/>And from the borders of Nephthali, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Manasses, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:4</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:4"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:5"/>And from the borders of Manasses, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Ephraim, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:5</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:5"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:6"/>And from the borders of Ephraim, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Rouben, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:6</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:6"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:7"/>And from the borders of Rouben, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Ioudas, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:7"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:8"/>And from the borders of Ioudas, from those eastward as far as those seaward, shall be the first fruit of what is set apart, twenty-five thousand in width and in length, just like one of the portions from those eastward and as far as those seaward, and that which is holy shall be in their midst,<verse eid="EZK 48:8"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:9"/>a first fruit, which they shall set apart for the Lord, in length twenty-five thousand and in width twenty-five thousand.<verse eid="EZK 48:9"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:10"/>Of these shall be the first fruit of the holies: the priests shall have twenty-five thousand northward and seaward; in breadth it shall be ten thousand, and southward twenty-five thousand in length, and the mountain of the holies shall be in his<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'Ioudas'</char></note> midst.<verse eid="EZK 48:10"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:11"/>To the consecrated priests, sons of Saddouk, who keep the guard over the house, who did not go astray in the straying of the sons of Israel as the Leuites went astray,<verse eid="EZK 48:11"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:12"/>to them shall also be the first fruit as given from the first fruits of the land, a holy of holies away from the borders of the Leuites.<verse eid="EZK 48:12"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:13"/>Now to the Leuites shall belong the parts next to the borders of the priests, in length twenty-five thousand and in width ten thousand, its whole length twenty-five thousand, and in width twenty thousand.<verse eid="EZK 48:13"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:14"/>Of it nothing shall be sold, neither shall anything be measured out, nor shall the firstlings of the land be removed, for it is something holy to the Lord.<verse eid="EZK 48:14"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:15"/>Now the five thousand in breadth, which are left over, in addition to the twenty-five thousand<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:15</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'the twenty-five thousand':  Possibly = 'the length'</char></note>-- it shall be an outer wall for the city, for habitation and as space for him<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:15</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'Ioudas'</char></note>, and the city shall be in his midst.<verse eid="EZK 48:15"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:16"/>And these are its<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'what is in excess'</char></note> measurements: from those northward, four thousand five hundred, and from those southward, four thousand five hundred, and from those eastward, four thousand five hundred, and from those seaward, four thousand five hundred.<verse eid="EZK 48:16"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:17"/>And a space shall belong to the city: northward, two hundred fifty, and southward, two hundred fifty, and eastward, two hundred fifty, and seaward, two hundred fifty.<verse eid="EZK 48:17"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:18"/>And what is in excess of the length, which is next to the first fruits of the holies, ten thousand eastward and ten thousand seaward, they also shall be the first fruits of what is holy, and its products shall be for bread for the workers of the city.<verse eid="EZK 48:18"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:19"/>But the workers of the city, out of all the tribes of Israel, shall cultivate it.<verse eid="EZK 48:19"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:20"/>The entire first fruit shall be twenty-five thousand by twenty-five thousand. You shall set apart of it<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:20</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'on either side of the holy portion'</char></note>, being square, the first fruit of what is holy, away from the possession of the city.<verse eid="EZK 48:20"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:21"/>Now, what is in excess belongs to the leader from this and from this<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'from this and from this':  Possibly 'on this side and on that side'</char></note> from the first fruits of what is holy and to the possession of the city, in length, to twenty-five thousand, as far as the borders eastward and seaward, to twenty-five thousand as far as the borders that are seaward, being next to the portions of the leader. And it shall be the first fruit of the holies and the holy precinct of the house in its midst.<verse eid="EZK 48:21"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:22"/>And some of the possession of the Leuites and some of the possession of the city shall be in the midst of the leaders. Between the borders of Ioudas and the borders of Beniamin shall belong to the leaders.<verse eid="EZK 48:22"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:23"/>As for what is in excess of the tribes: from the borders eastward as far as those seaward: of Beniamin, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:23</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:23"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:24"/>And from the borders of Beniamin, from those eastward as far as those seaward: of Symeon, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:24</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:24"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:25"/>And from the borders of Symeon, from those eastward as far as those seaward: for Issachar, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:25"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:26"/>And away from the borders of Issachar, from those eastward as far as those seaward: Zaboulon, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:26</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:26"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:27"/>And from the borders of Zaboulon, from those eastward as far as those seaward: Gad, one<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">48:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'portion' or 'tribe'</char></note>.<verse eid="EZK 48:27"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:28"/>And from the borders of Gad as far as those southwestward-- and his borders shall be from Thaiman and an inheritance of the water of Marimoth Kades as far as the great sea.<verse eid="EZK 48:28"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:29"/>This is the land that you shall assign by lot to the tribes of Israel, and these are their divisions, says the Lord.<verse eid="EZK 48:29"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:30"/>And these are the exits of the city: those northward, four thousand five hundred by measure.<verse eid="EZK 48:30"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:31"/>And the gates of the city shall be after the names of the tribes of Israel: three gates northward: gate of Rouben, one, and gate of Ioudas, one, and gate of Leui, one.<verse eid="EZK 48:31"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:32"/>And the ones to eastward: four thousand five hundred, and three gates: gate of Ioseph, one, and gate of Beniamin, one, and gate of Dan, one.<verse eid="EZK 48:32"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:33"/>And the ones southward: four thousand five hundred by measure, and three gates: gate of Symeon, one, and gate of Issachar, one, and gate of Zaboulon, one.<verse eid="EZK 48:33"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:34"/>And the ones to the sea shall be four thousand five hundred by measure, and three gates: gate of Gad, one, and gate of Aser, one, and gate of Nephthali, one.<verse eid="EZK 48:34"/>

<verse sid="EZK 48:35"/>Encirclement: eighteen thousand. And the name of the city: after whatever day it comes to be, it shall be its name.<verse eid="EZK 48:35"/>
</_X_chapter></_X_book></_X_usx>